&lt;h1 id="how-to-add-a-profile-image-to-your-validator-for-wm-explorer">How to add a profile image to your validator for WM Explorer?&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>&lt;strong>Written by Nodebase Team member &lt;a href="https://twitter.com/BKINDSPO">Gertjan&lt;/a>&lt;/strong>&lt;/p>
&lt;ol>
&lt;li>Go to the website &lt;a href="https://keybase.io">https://keybase.io&lt;/a>&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Create an account. This can be done by going to &amp;ldquo;Login&amp;rdquo; and after that choosing for &amp;ldquo;Join Keybase&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Test if your account is working properly&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Logout of your account. On the home page of Keybase click the button &amp;ldquo;Install&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Select the correct operating system and install the software&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Start the Keybase client on you computer and login with the account you created in step 2&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Change your profile image. This is the image that will show up in WM Explorer as your validator image&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Create a PGP key by selecting &amp;ldquo;Add a PGP key&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Choose &amp;ldquo;Get a new PGP key&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Fill in the form and click &amp;ldquo;Let the math begin&amp;rdquo;&lt;/li>
&lt;li>Click on the button &amp;ldquo;Done&amp;rdquo; in the dialog after&lt;/li>
&lt;li>You can now see a 16 character PGP key&lt;/li>
&lt;li>On your validator run the following command:&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;div style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#433e56;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">
&lt;table style="border-spacing:0;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;">&lt;tr>&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#433e56;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code>&lt;span style="white-space:pre;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1
&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>
&lt;td style="vertical-align:top;padding:0;margin:0;border:0;;width:100%">
&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#433e56;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-go" data-lang="go">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>ayad tx staking edit&lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">-&lt;/span>validator &lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">--&lt;/span>identity=&lt;span style="color:#1bc5e0">&amp;#34;16 character PGP key&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">--&lt;/span>from &amp;lt;operator name&amp;gt; &lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">--&lt;/span>home &lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">/&lt;/span>opt&lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">/&lt;/span>aya&lt;span style="color:#ffb8d1">/&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/td>&lt;/tr>&lt;/table>
&lt;/div>
&lt;/div>
&lt;ol start="14">
&lt;li>A transaction hash (txhash) is returned. Check in WM Explorer if the transaction was successful. If not, run
the command in step 13 again&lt;/li>
&lt;li>After a successful transaction, your profile image will appear in WM Explorer&lt;/li>
&lt;/ol></description></item></channel></rss>